<subSubSection id="3611A07A8F0D5CB74603058893EAA6A6" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="CC87A12E252C71E0AC6E67CE7ADFC00D" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="188193BCD7F0A01A7A82B8B1C134C9C0" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
This species has a broad distribution from Ecuador to Peru between 2100- 3200 m (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="06AB2F36CAEE226793AC7D7D3F9F2EA7" captionStart="Figure 93" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 93. Distribution of examined specimens of the genera Gaujonia and Gaujoptera." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.985.51622.figure93" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471615" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">93</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
