<paragraph id="EBE0A2C70132484F93D661FAE1408D08" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="51592B2A9725D6E52160DCF868FAC8EC" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C48D6550DE70F538CFA42A4DF5E4BFDD" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="DBB18DC82273E3110614F73BE54BF063" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AD861A5D15057582322A9CA66683C1A5" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
The holotype of 
<taxonomicName id="717E7C315E5DC854E87C7B44CB7706FA" authorityName="Martinez" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Gaujonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Gaujonia chiqyaq" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chiqyaq">
<emphasis id="744D63D1253FD8A9A3CDCABA3C3DAB8A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Gaujonia chiqyaq</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
closely resembles the type specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="F9E82018DD6A399D014E960A5BD58176" authorityName="Dognin" authorityYear="1891" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Gaujonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Gaujonia arbosi" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arbosi">
<emphasis id="ACB157658AE7EB4CBC92F6F970FD46CE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Gaujonia arbosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A8E75AA9C21F91280A9F98EACA6450AF" captionStart="Figures 26–42" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 26 - 42. Adult habitus of Gaujonia, Gaujoptera, and Millerana species 26 Gaujonia arbosi, ♂, MGCL, Napo, Ecuador 27 G. bichu, ♂, holotype, FSU, Zamora-Chinchipe, Ecuador 28 G. bichu, ♂, paratype, FSU, Loja, Ecuador 29 G. chiqyaq, ♂, paratype, MGCL, Marinio, Colombia 30 G. kanakusika, ♂, holotype, MGCL, Cundinamarca, Colombia 31 G. sourakovi, ♂, holotype, MGCL, Cusco, Peru 32 G. arbosi, ♀, MGCL, Napo, Ecuador 33 G. chiqyaq, ♀, holotype, MGCL, Marinio, Colombia 34 G. kanakusika, ♀, paratype, MGCL, Cundinamarca, Colombia 35 Gaujoptera amsa, ♂, holotype, MGCL, Cotapata, Bolivia 36 G. amsa, ♂, paratype, MGCL, Junin, Peru 37 Millerana arbosioides, ♂, MGCL, Carchi, Ecuador 38 M. austini, ♂, holotype, CUIC, Cotopaxi, Ecuador 39 M. matthewsae, ♂, holotype, MGCL, Ancash, Peru 40 M. cundinamarquensis, ♂, holotype, MGCL, Cundinamarca, Colombia 41 M. tigrina, ♂, holotype, MGCL, Carchi, Ecuador 42 M. cajas, ♂, holotype, MGCL, Azuay, Ecuador." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.985.51622.figures26-42" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471605" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">33</figureCitation>
) illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="247751405DE5D7D96ED2080D216982EE" author="Dognin, P" journalOrPublisher="Bureaux du journal &quot; Le Naturaliste &quot;, Paris, France" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" pagination="67 - 97" refId="B11" refString="Dognin, P, 1894. Lepidopteres de Loja et environs (equateur), descriptions d'especes nouvelles. In P. Dognin (Ed), Note sur la faune des lépidoptères de Loja (équateur), descriptions d'espèces nouvelles. Bureaux du journal &quot;Le Naturaliste&quot;, Paris, France 3 (17): 67 - 97" title="Lepidopteres de Loja et environs (equateur), descriptions d'especes nouvelles. In P. Dognin (Ed), Note sur la faune des le ́ pidopte ̀ res de Loja (e ́ quateur), descriptions d'espe ̀ ces nouvelles." volume="3" year="1894">Dognin (1894)</bibRefCitation>
. However, it is a different species from the lectotype of 
<taxonomicName id="B62DD605BC0CC1DD82906935426FDA31" genus="G." lsidName="G. arbosi" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" rank="species" species="arbosi">
<emphasis id="551008DE73D79ECFD18ADE0F18A1F570" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">G. arbosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, differing from it in characters of the male and female genitalia, thus it is here established as a new species. The holotype of 
<taxonomicName id="01FF34C4809CB4B0AB02257A71B9492B" authorityName="Dognin" authorityYear="1891" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Gaujonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Gaujonia arbosi" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arbosi">
<emphasis id="51023AF112C6EAF8E4ECAC32636E441F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Gaujonia arbosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and most of the paratypes are well preserved. 
<bibRefCitation id="206AD74B341021AF32EE97D9A5A23238" author="Guevara, D" journalOrPublisher="Nuestra Ciencia" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" pagination="51 - 53" refId="B15" refString="Guevara, D, Romero, T, 2008. Las polillas tambien afectan la produccion forestal. Datos biologicos de Gaujonia arbosioides (Lepidoptera: Noctuidae). Nuestra Ciencia 10: 51 - 53" title="Las polillas tambien afectan la produccion forestal. Datos biologicos de Gaujonia arbosioides (Lepidoptera: Noctuidae)." volume="10" year="2008">Guevara and Romero (2008)</bibRefCitation>
misidentified this species as 
<taxonomicName id="01E5FAD596613180551B397F7ADDF87F" authorityName="Dognin" authorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Gaujonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Gaujonia arbosioides" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arbosioides">
<emphasis id="790B4ACB3C7DC21FF87267C05D35547E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Gaujonia arbosioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is placed in a different genus (see 
<taxonomicName id="1324F7AB3721F815CA68B9BCB2157411" authority="Martinez, 2020" authorityName="Martinez" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Martinez" baseAuthorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Millerana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Millerana arbosioides" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arbosioides">
<emphasis id="B589613A8B9C6EA032849EFB2B955708" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Millerana arbosioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remarks).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
